title: For Trade:  Remington 12 ga. SxS
postcontent:
Remington model 1900 side by side in 12 ga.  Double triggers and extractors.  Works perfectly and locks up tight--I just shot four rounds of skeet with it (that's 100 shells, for those of you who don't know) with no problems whatsoever.  Has some cosmetic flaws, but fewer than you'd expect for its age: some marks on the wood, a couple of dings near the end of the barrels, and some corrosion patches in the bore, but nothing that affects safety or function.  The receiver internals are clean and corrosion-free.  The lever return spring is brand new.  

It would make a great hunting gun: robust, reliable, well-balanced, and not so fancy that you'd be worrying about messing it up.

It would also be a great gun to coach for cowboy action:  none of the barrel dings are within the first 18 inches, so they'd go away, and the chambers don't need to be reamed--they are already open enough to shake the empties out.

postcontent:
New in package. 

Molded polymer stock provides maximum comfort, speed, and freedom of movement for operators wearing body armor in CQC situations. Same topside contours as a standard M4 carbine stock allow the shooter to maintain a solid cheekweld when firing, but overall length is slightly shortened to maintain correct length of pull. The deeper, curved underside is angled so the lower tip rides comfortably on the upper chest or collarbone in a forward, high carry position near the dominant eye; keeps the sights and barrel close to the line of sight, ready to be engaged with minimal head movement.

Forward carry also provides better armor protection than the traditional angled stance that leaves the vulnerable arm holes exposed to threats. Made of lightweight, glass reinforced composite polycarbonate specially formulated for maximum impact and heat resistance. Reinforced at stress points for added strength. Aggressive checkering on contact surfaces minimize slippage.

Matte black finish accepts most paints, so you can customize the color of your Duostock to fit your tactical requirements. Universal fits all M4-type buffer tubes. Sand interior to fit oversized tubes. Colt model provides a snug fit without “play” on the narrower-diameter buffer tube of Mil-Spec M4 carbines.

This is compatible with Gen 1, 2 or 3. It is not compatible with Glock Gen 4 - sorry! This kit is in great condition and comes w/ all factory accessories. I'm including an extra 10 rd magazine. Price is $325.

Item Description:

These kits are had to find because the manufacturer Advantage Arms are working a large commercial contract and kits sold to individuals are extremely hard to find right now. This is a valuable training aid to maintain proficiency, train new shooters, or just to casually plink with. It is very reliable & easy to install.

For anyone who shoots very much ( or would like to shoot more) it can easily pay for itself in just one year. Training sessions are more enjoyable/ affordable when each shot is only $ .03-.04 per shot instead of $ .25 - .35.

FEATURES OF OUR CONVERSION KIT:


1. ADJUSTABLE SIGHTS The front and rear sights are removable GLOCK OEM sights. The rear sight is adjustable for both windage and elevation.

2. LAST ROUND LOCK OPEN The slide will lock open after the last round in the magazine has been fired. Our unique patented magazine design and heat-treated steel lock open insert allows us to offer this special and desirable feature which you can only find on 'Advantage Arms' .22LR GLOCK conversion kits. 3. FINISH All Aluminum parts are Anodized Per Mil-A-8625 with a matte black finish. All steel parts are heat treated with a Black Oxide Finish. The barrel is made from heat treated 416 Stainless Steel.

Now slide the "Advantage Arms" slide onto theframe, until it engages with the slide lock. Check to make sure that the slide lock is in its most upward position. Insert the conversion magazine. You are now ready to shoot.

5. INEXPENSIVE .22LR AMMO Never worry about leaving the range early because you don't want to use any more expensive ammo.

6. IMPROVED ACCURACY Because of less recoil, shooting the .22LR rounds in your Glock will improve your accuracy and get you used to the same look, feel and gun weight you are used to. The only difference is the ammo and cost of each round.

These are extremely hard to find kits in this size!
